  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7074 sitting below the 7099 flip strike in PIN regime, dealers are actively buying the dip as their long gamma position requires them to hedge by purchasing futures into weakness. The massive +6841M gamma wall at 7200 creates strong resistance where dealers will aggressively sell any rallies, while the -1078M negative gamma pocket at 7065 provides support through dealer buying. Key levels to watch: 7065 downside support, 7099 regime flip, and the heavy 7100/7150/7200 gamma wall cluster that should cap upside momentum.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce back toward 7100 with strong resistance at the 7150-7200 zone.",
